[5] Cholera, 2007 - Nigeria
Date: Thu 31 Jan 2008
Source: AllAfrica.com, This Day (Lagos) report [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200801310357.html>


In 2007, a total of 1444 cases and 34 deaths were recorded from cholera
outbreaks nationwide. The outbreaks occurred in Borno, Jigawa, Bauchi,
Kaduna, Edo, Delta, and Bayelsa States.

[byline: Onwuka Nzeshi]

