[6] Cholera, gastroenteritis - India: (Karnataka)
Date: Wed 30 Jan 2008
Source: Deccan Herald [edited]
<http://www.deccanherald.com/Content/Jan302008/scroll2008013049379.asp?section=frontpagenews>


One confirmed case of cholera was reported in Bangalore on Tuesday [29 Jan
20008], while 17 people suspected of harboring the disease have been
referred to Isolation Hospital by doctors in and around Bharatinagar.
According to highly placed sources in Bowring Hospital, a 28 year old has
tested positive for cholera and has been referred to Isolation Hospital.

Fresh cases of gastroenteritis continued to be reported at hospitals. The
Thimmaiah Road Corporation Maternity Hospital reported 427 fresh
gastroenteritis cases from Tuesday morning [29 Jan 2008] till midnight, of
whom 4 have been referred to Isolation hospital with suspected cholera.
"Due to severe dehydration, 14 persons were admitted, of whom 10 were
discharged by late night," said Dr S Sujatha. St Philomena's Hospital had
12 gastroenteritis cases. "We have referred all of them to go to Isolation
hospital for cholera check-up," said Dr Mansoor Pasha, casualty medical
officer.

One cholera suspect figured among 20 cases reported at G M Nursing Home,
near Lavanya theatre. "A 75 year old was shifted to Isolation Hospital,"
said Dr Murali, managing director.

BBMP [Bruhat Bangalore Mahanagara Palike -- the new administrative body
responsible for the civic and infrastructural assets of the city of
Bangalore. - CopyEd.MJ] chief health officer Dr LT Gayatri claimed there
were 200 fresh cases of gastroenteritis in Bharatinagar and no one was
critical. She said the disease had not spread to other areas. The Palike
has set up help desks in hospitals.

--
