[7] Cholera, gastroenteritis - India: (Karnataka)
Date: Thu 31 Jan 2008
Source: The Hindu [edited]
<http://www.hindu.com/2008/01/31/stories/2008013161020300.htm>


A total of 5 people have tested positive for cholera but it cannot be
termed an outbreak as the cases are from different parts of Bangalore,
sources at the Department of Health and Family Welfare said on Wednesday
[29 Jan 2008].

The 5 affected by cholera are from Central Street in Neelasandra, Cox Town,
Dooravaninagar, Economically Weaker Section Quarters in Kormanagala and
Hoskote, sources added. No person has tested positive for cholera at
Bharathinagar, where the 1st case of gastroenteritis was reported.

The 19 samples sent to the Public Health Institute (PHI) on Tuesday [29 Jan
2008] from the Epidemic Diseases Hospital and the Bruhat Bangalore
Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) hospital in Bharathinagar have tested negative. At
the BBMP hospital in Bharathinagar, 206 people were treated as outpatients
on Wednesday [30 Jan 2008] and the number of people in the area complaining
of diarrhea and vomiting has come down, sources said. R Murali Krishna,
doctor at GM Hospital in Bharathinagar, said only 5 persons were treated
for symptoms of gastroenteritis and only one admitted.

Shivaram, joint director (Communicable Diseases) at the Department of
Health and Family Welfare, said that Bangalore Urban District (which
includes Bangalore city) reported only 28 cases of cholera in the last 2 years.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Karnataka is a state in the southern part of India [known as the State of
Mysore until 1973]. Bangalore is the capital city of the state, which can
be seen on a map at <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karnataka>. - Mod.LL]

